criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  acute myocardial infarction with Killip I classification, hemodynamic stability,
             between 24 and 72 hours post event;

          -  agreement to participate in the study, according written informed consent;

          -  45 to 80 years old age.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  unstable angina;

          -  systolic blood pressure < 80 mmHg;

          -  patients who presented ST elevation > 2 mm or with second-degree atrioventricular
             block;

          -  presence of pacemaker.
